Housing Development’s First-Quarter Profit Beats Estimates

-- B y   P o o j a   T h a k u r
-- 
2011-08-12T06:13:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/housing-development-s-first-quarter-profit-beats-estimates.html
Housing Development & Infrastructure
Ltd. (HDIL) ,  India ’s fourth-largest developer, reported a first-quarter
that beat analysts’ estimates.  Profit in the quarter ended June 30 fell 11 percent to 2.09
billion rupees ($46 million). That was higher than the 1.74
billion rupee median of 12 estimates compiled by Bloomberg.
Sales climbed 11 percent to 5.02 billion rupees, beating the
4.43 billion rupee median estimate.  Home prices in Mumbai, India’s most expensive property
market, increased to a record 9,716 rupees a square foot in the
quarter, according to Liases Foras Real Estate Rating & Research
Pvt., a Mumbai real-estate research company.  Shares of Mumbai-based Housing Development rose 2.3 percent
to 119.45 rupees as of 11:17 a.m. in  Mumbai  trading.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pooja Thakur in Mumbai at 
